===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|vérisimilitude}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|vērīsimilitūdō||likeness to truth}}, more correctly written separately as {{m|la|vērī similitūdō||}}; from {{m|la|vērī||}}, genitive singular of {{m|la|vērus||true, real}}, + {{m|la|similitūdō||likeness, resemblance}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/vɛrɪsɪˈmɪlɪtjuːd/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The property of seeming [[true]], of resembling reality; resemblance to reality, [[realism]].
# A [[statement]] which merely [[appear]]s to be [[true]].
# {{lb|en|fiction}} Faithfulness to its own rules; internal [[cohesion]].

